## ApiSources-A3 Model-First Agent Configuration Architecture
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:both, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G1, ApiSources-G3

### Problem

The current tier-based model selection forces agents to choose from 5 abstract tiers (min/lite/mid/pro/max). But a concrete ApiSource may only have 1–3 models, not covering all tiers. The fallback-downgrade logic in `resolve_model()` silently picks a different model than intended, and users have no way to directly control which specific model an agent uses.

### Solution

Flip the selection axis: **AgentConfig references a concrete model by ID**, not a tier. The tier becomes a display tag on the model, useful for UX grouping and recommendation but never used as a selection key.

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Config Layer"
        AC[AgentConfig] -->|model_id| MD[ModelDefinition]
        MD -->|belongs to| AS[ApiSource]
        MD -->|tagged| MT[ModelTier label]
    end
    subgraph "Resolution"
        RM[resolve_model] -->|lookup model_id in ApiSource.models| MD
        RM -->|found| MC[ModelConfig: provider + model + params]
        RM -->|not found| FB[Fallback: first model in ApiSource]
    end
    subgraph "UI"
        SEL[Model Selector] -->|lists| MODELS[ApiSource.models]
        MODELS -->|shows tier badge| MT
    end
```

### Data Model Change

**Before** (current code at `backend/src/relay/config.rs:370-400`):
```
AgentConfig { api_source_id, model_tier: ModelTier }
                           ↓
resolve_model: find model WHERE tier == model_tier (with downgrade walk)
```

**After** (target):
```
AgentConfig { api_source_id, model_id: String, model_tier: ModelTier (deprecated) }
                           ↓
resolve_model: find model WHERE id == model_id (direct lookup)
assign_model_ids: if model_id empty, convert model_tier → first matching model
```

### Key Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Selection key | `model_id` (String) | Direct reference, no ambiguity, no fallback logic needed |
| Tier role | Display tag only | Still useful for UX grouping, recommendation badges, cost estimation |
| model_id scope | Scoped to ApiSource | Same model_id can exist in different sources (e.g., "claude-sonnet-4-20250514") |
| Fallback | First model in ApiSource | Only when model_id is invalid/removed; should be rare |
| Default configs | Reference concrete model IDs | Defaults choose specific models from the first available ApiSource |
| Migration | Auto-convert: tier → first matching model | Transparent upgrade for existing configs |
| Backward compat | Keep `model_tier` field with `#[serde(default)]` | Old JSON configs still deserialize; migration fills `model_id` |

### Model Resolution Sequence

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant O as Orchestrator
    participant R as resolve_model()
    participant AS as ApiSource
    participant M as ModelDefinition

    O->>R: resolve(AgentConfig)
    R->>AS: find by api_source_id
    alt api_source_id valid
        R->>AS: find model by model_id
        alt model_id found
            R->>M: return ModelConfig(provider, model_id, params)
        else model_id not found (removed/renamed)
            R->>M: fallback to AS.models[0]
            Note over R: Log warning: model_id not found
        end
    else api_source_id invalid
        R->>AS: use first ApiSource
        R->>M: fallback to AS.models[0]
        Note over R: Log warning: api_source not found
    end
```

### Trigger Condition
`resolve_model()` is called whenever an agent is spawned: relay pipeline step, chat turn, or errand dispatch.

### Data Flow
```
[AgentConfig: api_source_id + model_id] → [lookup ApiSource] → [find ModelDefinition by id] → [ModelConfig]
```

### Design Highlight
By storing `model_id` instead of `model_tier`, we eliminate the entire downgrade-walk logic (lines 548-586 in current config.rs) and give users direct control. The tier tag remains for UX convenience — showing "Mid" next to "claude-sonnet-4-20250514" helps users understand cost/capability without forcing them into a rigid hierarchy.

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| **model_id direct reference (chosen)** | Exact control, no silent downgrades, simpler code | Must update when models are removed/renamed |
| Tier with fallback walk (current) | Works with partial tier coverage | Silent downgrades, user confusion |
| Tier + model override | Backwards compatible | Two selection axes = confusion |

### Verified Code Locations

| Component | File | Lines |
|-----------|------|-------|
| `AgentConfig` struct (current) | `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | ~370-400 |
| `resolve_model()` (current tier walk) | `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | ~548-586 |
| `generate_default_agents_with_source()` | `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | ~458-490 |
| `load_or_generate_agent_configs()` | `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | ~498-527 |
| `RelayRegistry` (uses configs) | `backend/src/relay/mod.rs` | ~48-58 |
| `AgentConfigDto` (current) | `frontend/src/composables/useAgentConfigs.ts` | ~8-22 |
| `ApiSource` type | `frontend/src/composables/useApiSources.ts` | ~9-22 |
| `AgentsConfigView` (tier dropdown) | `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue` | ~1-902 |

## ApiSources-A3 Model-First Agent Configuration Architecture
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:both, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G1, ApiSources-G3

### Problem

The current tier-based model selection forces agents to choose from 5 abstract tiers (min/lite/mid/pro/max). But a concrete ApiSource may only have 1–3 models, not covering all tiers. The fallback-downgrade logic in `resolve_model()` silently picks a different model than intended, and users have no way to directly control which specific model an agent uses.

### Solution

Flip the selection axis: **AgentConfig references a concrete model by ID**, not a tier. The tier becomes a display tag on the model, useful for UX grouping and recommendation but never used as a selection key.

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Config Layer"
        AC[AgentConfig] -->|model_id| MD[ModelDefinition]
        MD -->|belongs to| AS[ApiSource]
        MD -->|tagged| MT[ModelTier label]
    end
    subgraph "Resolution"
        RM[resolve_model] -->|lookup model_id in ApiSource.models| MD
        RM -->|found| MC[ModelConfig: provider + model + params]
        RM -->|not found| FB[Fallback: first model in ApiSource]
    end
    subgraph "UI"
        SEL[Model Selector] -->|lists| MODELS[ApiSource.models]
        MODELS -->|shows tier badge| MT
    end
```

