By storing `model_id` instead of `model_tier`, we eliminate the entire downgrade-walk logic (lines 548-586 in current config.rs) and give users direct control. The tier tag remains for UX convenience — showing "Mid" next to "claude-sonnet-4-20250514" helps users understand cost/capability without forcing them into a rigid hierarchy.

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| **model_id direct reference (chosen)** | Exact control, no silent downgrades, simpler code | Must update when models are removed/renamed |
| Tier with fallback walk (current) | Works with partial tier coverage | Silent downgrades, user confusion |
| Tier + model override | Backwards compatible | Two selection axes = confusion |

### Verified Code Locations

| Component | File | Lines |
|-----------|------|-------|
| `AgentConfig` struct (current) | `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | ~370-400 |
| `resolve_model()` (current tier walk) | `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | ~548-586 |
| `generate_default_agents_with_source()` | `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | ~458-490 |
| `load_or_generate_agent_configs()` | `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | ~495-530 |
| `RelayRegistry` (uses configs) | `backend/src/relay/mod.rs` | ~48-58 |
| `AgentConfigDto` (current) | `frontend/src/composables/useAgentConfigs.ts` | ~8-22 |
| `ApiSource` type | `frontend/src/composables/useApiSources.ts` | ~9-22 |
