**Depends on:** ApiSources-G1, ApiSources-G3

### Problem

The current tier-based model selection forces agents to choose from 5 abstract tiers (min/lite/mid/pro/max). But a concrete ApiSource may only have 1–3 models, not covering all tiers. The fallback-downgrade logic in `resolve_model()` (lines 548–586 of `backend/src/relay/config.rs`) silently picks a different model than intended, and users have no way to directly control which specific model an agent uses.

