### Data Flow
```
[AgentConfig: api_source_id + model_id] → [lookup ApiSource] → [find ModelDefinition by id] → [ModelConfig]
```

### Design Highlight
By storing `model_id` instead of `model_tier`, we eliminate the entire downgrade-walk logic and give users direct control. The tier tag remains for UX convenience — showing "Mid" next to "claude-sonnet-4-20250514" helps users understand cost/capability without forcing them into a rigid hierarchy.

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| **model_id direct reference (chosen)** | Exact control, no silent downgrades, simpler code | Must update when models are removed/renamed |
| Tier with fallback walk (current) | Works with partial tier coverage | Silent downgrades, user confusion |
| Tier + model override | Backwards compatible | Two selection axes = confusion |
